'''Cătălin Adrian Botezatu''' ({{IPA-ro|kətəˈlin boteˈzatu}}; born 3 December 1966)<ref name=Biografie>{{cite web |title=Biografie |url=http://www.catalinbotezatu.ro/catalin-botezatu-biografie.html |work=catalinbotezatu.ro |publisher=catalinbotezatu |accessdate=5 April 2012 }}</ref> is a [[Romania]]n [[model (person)|model]], [[fashion designer]], [[media personality]] and [[businessperson]].

Botezatu attended a fashion house in [[Bucharest]], and in 1985 he qualified as a [[model (person)|model]] for presentations abroad. After only a few months, he was awarded the title “European Male Model of the Year”.<ref name=Bote>{{cite web |title=Catalin Botezatu’s Romanian Couture Designs at Fashion Week 2012 |url=http://www.worldlibertytv.org/nyc/?p=3485 |work=worldlibertytv.org |publisher=worldlibertytv |accessdate=5 April 2012 }}</ref> Later, he attended the European Institute of Fashion in [[Milan]], where he had the late fashion designer [[Gianni Versace]] as a teacher. Later  Botezatu became director of the Fashion House style “Europe” in [[Bucharest]]. He eventually founded his own fashion house, “Delphi”.<ref name="Bote"/>

Since the early 2010s, Botezatu has hosted several [[reality television]] programs on [[Antena 1 (Romania)|Antena 1]], such as ''[[Next Top Model (Romania)|Next Top Model]]'', ''[[The Bachelor (U.S. TV series)|Burlacul]]'' and ''[[The Bachelorette|Burlăciţa]]''.

