In computing, '''hyperscale''' is the ability of an architecture to scale appropriately as increased demand is added to the system. This typically involves the ability to seamlessly provision and add compute, memory, networking, and storage resources to a given node or set of nodes that make up a larger [[computing]], [[distributed computing]], or [[grid computing]] environment. Hyperscale computing is necessary in order to build a robust and scalable [[Cloud Computing|cloud]], [[Big Data|big data]], [[MapReduce|map reduce]], or [[Clustered file system|distributed storage]] system and is often associated with the infrastructure required to run large distributed sites such as [[Facebook]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Miller|first=Rich|title=A Hyper-Scale Cloud Data Center, Seen From the Clouds|url=http://www.datacenterknowledge.com/archives/2012/11/06/facebook-lulea-aerial-view/|publisher=Data Center Knowledge}}</ref>, [[Google]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Google Data Centers|url=https://www.google.com/about/datacenters/gallery/#/|publisher=Google}}</ref>, [[Microsoft]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Microsoft Expands Its Hyperscale Cloud Footprint|url=http://www.eweek.com/cloud/microsoft-expands-its-hyperscale-cloud-footprint.html|publisher=eweek.com}}</ref>, [[Amazon.com|Amazon]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Furrier|first=John|title=Fusion-io Launched New Hyperscale Flash Product to Scale Data Centers for Enterprises, Not Just Facebook|url=http://siliconangle.com/blog/2013/01/17/fusion-io-launched-new-hyperscale-flash-product-to-scale-data-centers-for-enterprises-not-just-facebook/|publisher=Silicon Angle}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Rouse|first=Margaret|title=Definition: Hyperscale Computing|url=http://whatis.techtarget.com/definition/hyperscale-computing|publisher=TechTarget}}</ref>, or [[Oracle Corporation|Oracle]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cloud.oracle.com/en_US/data-mgmt|title=Data Management {{!}} Oracle Cloud|website=cloud.oracle.com|language=en|access-date=2018-07-11}}</ref>. Companies like [[Ericsson]] and [[Intel]] provide hyperscale infrastructure kits for IT service providers.<ref>http://www.datacenterdynamics.com/content-tracks/servers-storage/ericsson-to-sell-intels-hyperscale-kit-to-network-operators/93484.fullarticle</ref>
